{
  "name": "peepshow",
  "version": "0.8.1",
  "description": "Turn videos + animated images (GIF/APNG/WebP) into a timeline of still frames + audio transcript + a self-contained HTML report so LLMs can 'watch', 'listen', and write their analysis back. Second ffmpeg pass extracts an audio track; whisper.cpp or openai/groq/deepgram/assemblyai transcribe it. CLI + Claude Code plugin with 71 pluggable sinks across SQL (SQLite, Postgres, MongoDB), vector + memory (Chroma, Qdrant, Pinecone, pgvector, Weaviate, Milvus, MemPalace, Zep, Mem0, Letta), storage (S3-compatible, GCS, Firebase Storage, Azure Blob, Supabase, Dropbox, Google Drive, Box, OpenAI Files), chat (Slack, Discord, MS Teams, Telegram, Mattermost, Rocket.Chat, Zulip, Matrix, WhatsApp, iMessage), issue trackers (Linear, Height, GitHub Issues, Jira, Asana, ClickUp, Shortcut, Trello), whiteboards (Miro, Figma), wiki + notes (Notion, Obsidian, Logseq, Outline, Confluence, Apple Notes, Bear), analytics + observability (PostHog, Plausible, Sentry, Datadog, New Relic, Honeycomb, PagerDuty, Opsgenie, Grafana Oncall, Mixpanel/Amplitude/Segment) and workflow glue (Webhook, GraphQL, IDE, Aider, Continue, Cody, Raycast, Pipedream, Zapier, Shortcuts, Apple Reminders, Things 3).",
  "type": "module",
  "license": "MIT",
  "author": {
    "name": "Tom Taylor",
    "url": "https://x.com/tom_taylor"
  },
